On the afternoon of April 4, four tourists climbed over the safety guardrail on the glass plank road on the west line of the top of Tianmen Mountain Scenic Area and jumped off the cliff. Three of them jumped down and one was stopped in time. However, because he had taken poison before jumping off the cliff, he died after rescue efforts failed.
According to the identity information of the cliff jumpers, they were from Fujian, Hebei, Henan and Sichuan, ranging in age from 22 to 33 years old, three men and one woman. After investigation by the public security department, it was initially determined based on the suicide note that the four people committed suicide.
